events.name: New York Knicks at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Julius Randle answered Kristaps Porzingis' early flurry, and by the time the New York standout was done, he'd matched his career high in scoring.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle scores 46 as Knicks rally past Wizards 115-109

headlines.description: — The Atlanta Hawks returned from the All-Star break — and a coaching change — refreshed and motivated.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawks pull away in 1st half, rout Cavaliers 136-119

headlines.description: — The Milwaukee Bucks sure didn’t let Giannis Antetokounmpo’s early exit bother them Friday night as they rolled to their most-lopsided victory of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis exits early with knee issue; Bucks rip Heat 128-99

headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball had 32 points, 10 rebounds, eight assists and the dagger 3-pointer down the stretch to lead the Charlotte Hornets past the Minnesota Timberwolves 121-113 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaMelo Ball helps Hornets beat Timberwolves 121-113

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 32 points on 12-of-17 shooting and the Chicago Bulls drubbed the Brooklyn Nets 131-87 on Friday night to snap a six-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine, DeRozan lead Bulls to 131-87 rout of Nets

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — The Phoenix Suns are still looking forward to the debut of recently acquired superstar Kevin Durant.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker scores 25 points, Suns beat Thunder 124-115

events.name: Houston Rockets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Only last week ahead of the All-Star break did Klay Thompson even receive medical clearance to play on back-to-back nights, 13 months after his return from a more than 2 1/2-year absence recovering from knee and Achilles surgeries.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson scores 42 points, Warriors beat Rockets 116-101

headlines.description: — There were a couple moments Friday night when Sacramento coach Mike Brown wishes he could have enjoyed being a part of the second-highest scoring game in NBA history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings outlast Clippers 176-175 in double overtime
